page.title: 10WILSTER COPSE
page.content:
Wilster Copse consists of Oak, Ash, and Hazel overgrown with Brambles. It is inhabited by numerous birds, including Blackcaps and Nightingales. There are some reared pheasant for shooting and a litter of foxes. There are 10 beehives producing honey from Bluebells, Rose Madder and hedgerow blossoms.
Surrounding the wood are barley fields separated by large thick hedges. To the North wild cherries line Grims Ditch which is still well defined. This runs East-West into Netherton Hanging, a steep bank of deciduous wood recently part cleared, fenced, and replanted with conifers.
